Roxy Wallace was a bodyguard called Bob who struggled with depression . 
  She told her wife Jo that she wanted to live life as a woman and told her son William she was 'mummy Roxy' Roxy had become a full-time carer for William but the pair never really bonded . 
  She struggled with the belief that he was born into the wrong body . 
  Two years ago she began gender reassignment surgery . 
  She says she is now the 'luckiest woman in the world' and has mended her relationship with her son . 
 